  "doc_id": "37549",
  "text": "Zone 2 of the PAR contains the previously identified IL9R gene [CITATION_1] , starting at nucleotide 295 352. In addition, a novel gene was found starting at nucleotide 319 633 and ending <5 kb from the telomere-associated repeat sequence. This 5.5 kb genomic region shows high homology with >180 human ESTs and is also homologous to (though not previously noted) in subtelomeric sequence from chromosome 16p [CITATION_2] . The ESTs can be grouped into different subclasses of highly homologous transcripts (>98% identity). One (GenBank accession no. AI042587, from an IMAGE clone) was distinguishable from 16p sequence and other subclasses but identical to PAR sequence. When it was sequenced, the identity extended throughout its 962 bp. Detailed comparison of this cDNA with the genomic sequence revealed the last 4 exons, part of a fifth and a putative polyadenylation signal (AATAAA) 16 bp from the observed poly(A) tract. This partial gene, named CXYorf1, hybridized to at least four RNA species, including an abundant 2 kb transcript, in all adult human tissues examined (unpublished data). The sequence of CXYorf1 gives no obvious clues to its function, though a biological role could conceivably be related to its localization near the telomere (see Discussion).",
